<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10031153111794></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10031153111794><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=78732&mid=10031153111794>Heretic</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=78732&mid=10031153111794#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93468><span id=Guru>tochail the Wise</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>211 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Oct 14th 11:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.63]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>An open letter to the Scholarly Naldiin Aredhel'istar,<br>Sir:<br><br>I find your writings in stark contrast to the teachings expounded by the clerics of Tunare, and will point to two specific instances.&nbsp;&nbsp;I would encourage and enjoy an honest response to my observations, and pray that you do not take this post as a flame.<br><br>1)  The clerics of Tunare teach that Innoruuk was not the original god of the Elves, but that Tunare, the Mother, was the first god of the elves.  I would refer you to the (ooc starter kit) legend of the first king and queen, and the jealousy of Innoruuk at Tunare's perfect creations.  I would further suggest that your theory on the war between the elves is in error due to the idea that Dark Elves would ever come to the aid of a Dwarf.  I have never seen this happen, though admittedly, my knowledge is a bit limited in this regard.<br><br>2)  You state that "as a Dragon is to an Elf, so is Veeshan to the greater gods, such as Tunare.."  On what grounds do you base this assumption?  Do you have evidence that suggests Veeshan even still exists, and that through this existance, she can overpower the gods of Norrath?  I have walked the mountains of skyfire, and I have seen the dread wurms;  I know I would never stand a chance against one of those beasts, and yet, I know that I am not consumed or threatened by them.<br><br>In your response, most noble sir, I would like you to refer me to the locations of the libraries and vendors of lore that you have quoted.  I can easily travel the continents of Norrath, with the assistance of wizardly friends, so I have no worry over the distance needed in order to collect these writings.<br><br>Most humbly yours,<br>&nbsp;<br>Icewind Novastorm<br>Koada Dal Cleric of Tunare<br>&lt;&lt;Mith Marr&gt;&gt;</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
