ms.<br><br>The greatest creation of Tunare was the elves, yet both Kelethin and Felwithe would serve for little more than kindaling had the ring of scale not been parried by the Vampire Mistmoore (pre-Kunark Gm events made this abundantly clear--Venril Sather and Mayong Mistmoore both work activly against the dragons of kunark...)<br><br>And, as for Tunare's might, Woushi, a single true dragon, seems to hold her own within the Wakening Lands, the most sacred of Tunare's forests.  The Giants and the Dragons activly wage war accross tunare's forest, meaning that it cannot impede them.(THis is fact.  The dragons do hold thier own in the Wakening lands, with Woushi hunting Giants, and giants attempting to kill Woushi, seemingly ignorant of the powers of the forest)<br><br>And, to make the dominance of the Cystalline Dragon complete, Tunare is not even as large as one of Veeshan's single talons.  (this can be determined by sizing Tunare against the giant gashes in Velious)<br><br>That is All<br>&nbsp;<br>Naldiin Aredhel'istar<br>Magician, 52th Circle<br>&lt;Povar-Tarrew Artisiens&gt;<br>Xev Server</td></tr>
