<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100241029859407></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100241029859407><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=78732&mid=100241029859407>Mayong Mistmoore, Vampire Lord of Faydwer</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=78732&mid=100241029859407#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=78732><span id=Scholar>Naldiin the Wise</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>33 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 6th 7:18 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My observations reguarding Mayong Mistmoore...<br><br>For those of you who are not familair with Mistmoore, he is quiet possibly the most powerful being on Norrath.&nbsp;&nbsp;I attempt in this work to cover his hidden empire in detail with what is known.<br><br>Mayong Mistmoore himself is a Vampire of a dark Elven noble of long ago.  The location of his castle (The lesser Faydark) leads me to beleive that he lived (in the more traditional sense) before the break of the elven empire.  The great capital city of the elves was located then in the hills of shade, it was called Caerthiel.<br><br>A vampire's power increases exponetially as they age, and thus it is with Mayong.  He must have been a powerful spell caster in his life because he sems to have been the only living being able to keep his mind after transforming into the un-life.  Venril Sathir was thwarted by his son, and required the assistance of a god, and Miragul tried it alone, and failed.  Mayong is older than both of these creatures.  MUCH older.  Miragul made notes of Mayong's minions while he was still in erudin (one of the librarians there has a small scrap of Miragul's journal, for a small price.)<br><br>Mistmoore's power extends too every corner of Norrath.  He has cut much of the travel in Kunark to peices by heavy use of Drachnids.  Drachnids are half dark elves, half spiders, another foul experiment of Mayong's.  The drachnid's are based out of the Dreadlands, but have also set a practical siege upon the compound at Firiona Vie, all at the bidding of Mistmoore.  The ocean of tears also bears his mark, as a small contigent of his gragoyles.<br><br>Mayong Mistmoore's greatest power is located within his castle, which he is hardly ever present.  The entire grounds and castle are packed with creatures in thrall to the Vampire lord.  These include living well armed dark elves who bow before Mistmoore, as well as lesser vampiric servents.  Also full mindless undead (damphryes, will-sappers, etc) dwell within his castle, and a pack of blood wolves below it.  A renegade shadowed man is either held by spell or seeks asilum within the Castle, and will not attack anyone unless you have angered the Temple of Ro (he is renegade against his fellow shadowed men).  The scarecrows and Jack-o-lanterns in Unrest and the planes of Karana were created by a long dead minion of Mistmoore, as recorded in Miragul's journel.<br><br>The castle itself is a major obstacle in challenging Mistmoore.  Hidden within the Lesser Faydark, it is hard to assail due to the army of dark elves who dwell there, and it's position ontop a steep crag and over a narrow bridge.  It isn't a long jump of logic to say that the High elves and Wood Elves launched assalts upon it as they set up thier own cities, seeing as how Mistmoore is the effective simbol of everything they hate<br><br>Mistmoore himself does not follow any god.  He helped to defeat Lanys T'vl after she was disowned by Innoruuk, and complete Malevolence, but he does not follow Innoruuk.  He did not interfere when Cazic Thule took temporary control of the lesser faydark.  He did directly oppose the Ring of Scale, and by assosiation, Veeshan herself (as a Dragon is to an Elf, so is Veeshan to the greater gods, such as Tunare, Bertoxxulos, or Thule...).  This leads me to beleive that Mistmoore has nearly godlike powers on his own, otherwise he would have been smashed.<br><br>It is unknown his relationship with Miragul, although both knew of eachother.  It is similarly unknow how he treats with Venril Sathir, although i would assume decent relations, the castle in the dreadlands (Karnor's) is in Venril's hands, and the Drachnids in the Dreadlands seem to protect it.<br><br>Mistmoore opposes the joint Bard guilds, although the grivence is not known to this scholar (if you know, post it).<br><br>That is all.<br>&nbsp;<br>Naldiin Aredhel'istar<br>Magician, 52th Circle<br>&lt;Povar-Tarrew Artisiens&gt;<br>Xev Server</td></tr>
