<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100233493628711></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100233493628711><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=78732&mid=100233493628711>The crypt of Danlir, and the Kly</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=78732&mid=100233493628711#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=78732><span id=Scholar>Lord Naldiin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>33 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 5th 10:22 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>(This is under re-editing, just so that you know, and will be reposted above under the Kunark Thread)<br><br>My observations reguardling the inhabitants of the Crypt of Danlir...<br><br>As is well known, many creatures in what was the Crypt of Danlir, but could now be described more as the laboratory of the Kly, are unique in that place in Norrath.<br><br>The history behind the Crypt is not long.&nbsp;&nbsp;Danlir was a rich Iksar noble, who wished a secert burial when he died.  This the first several sets of tunnels were dug, he died, and was burried there.<br><br>This is infrence, but i belive that a group of Sarnak, under relegious or scientific motivations (either they couldn't preform thier FOUL experiments, or they couldn't practice thier relegion...) broke from the main Sarnak collective.  I say relegious, because many of the greater Kly are refered to rank-wise by what appears to be faith status (believer, follower, etc).<br><br>They 'set up shop' at the lowest levels...and began digging new caves.  Well adapt at mind control and coercion, they captured, instead of killed most of those that entered the crypt, creating an army of mindless minions.  Gnomes, Erudites, Tier'dal, and Iksar have all been seen there.  Oddly, although evidenced by the precense of thier heads in preservation jars, the froglocks have not been 'coerced' into joining the ranks of the Kly...but just killed instead.<br><br>The leader of the Kly, is simply named 'The Kly'.  (ooc: something like the Minoans, named because thier kings were all called Minos, which is now stipulated, is thier word for "king").  His room is adorned with two fine wooden shelf/cases with books and scrolls, presumably of research, and the already-mentioned froglock heads, (perhaps FOR experiments).<br><br>It is entirely possible that all the creatures in the crypt were created by the Kly to defend themselves.  The Kly look exactly like thier Sarnak brethern and on rare occasions (read: Gm event) have been known too help the Sarnak collective in battle.<br><br>That is all.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Naldiin Aredhel'istar<br>Magician, 52th Circle<br>&lt;Povar-Tarrew Artisiens&gt;<br>Xev Server</td></tr>
